					Latest Key Developments (Source: Significant Developments)




VITEC HOLDINGS announces business and capital alliance with Panasonic
Monday, 4 Apr 2016 03:30am EDT 
VITEC HOLDINGS CO LTD:Formed a business and capital alliance with Panasonic on April 4.VITEC HOLDINGS to transfer 87,999 shares of wholly owned subsidiary PTT Company Limited to Panasonic on June 30.Panasonic to hold 19.99 pct stake in PTT Company Limited after transfer.Says two entities will cooperate on procurement related business. 
			
Full Article





VITEC HOLDINGS lowers consolidated full-year outlook for FY 2016
Monday, 28 Mar 2016 04:00am EDT 
VITEC HOLDINGS CO LTD:Says the company reaffirmed the consolidated full-year outlook for revenue at 145,000 mln yen for the fiscal year ending March 31, 2016.Sees a decrease of operating profit forecast to 2,400 mln yen from 3,000 mln yen.Sees a decrease of ordinary profit forecast to 1,750 mln yen from 2,500 mln yen.Sees a decrease of net profit forecast to 1,200 mln yen from 1,700 mln yen.Sees a decrease of earnings per share to 87.77 yen from 124.41 yen.Says the impact of high-valued yen and reduction of output for China market in its device business and price downturn in its new electricity business as main reasons for the forecast. 
			
Full Article





VITEC HOLDINGS to issue mid-year dividend for FY 2016
Friday, 6 Nov 2015 01:00am EST 
VITEC HOLDINGS CO LTD:To issue a mid-year dividend of 25 yen per share to all the shareholders of record as of Sep. 30, for the fiscal year ending March 2016.Payment date Dec. 7.Says the dividend amount is in line with the latest forecast. 
			
Full Article





VITEC HOLDINGS lowers consolidated full-year net profit outlook for FY 2016
Friday, 6 Nov 2015 01:00am EST 
VITEC HOLDINGS CO LTD:Says the company reaffirmed the consolidated full-year outlook for revenue at 145,000 mln yen for the fiscal year ending March 2016.Sees a decrease of operating profit forecast to 3,000 mln yen from 3,500 mln yen.Sees a decrease of ordinary profit forecast to 2,500 mln yen from 3,000 mln yen.Sees a decrease of net profit forecast to 1,700 mln yen from 2,000 mln yen.Sees a decrease of earnings per share to 124.41 yen from 144.10 yen.Says profit outlook raised due to the improved profitability and cost reduction. 
			
