                                                Vitec Holdings Co Ltd
                                             Company Snapshot
                                            









                                            
	Vitec Holdings Co Ltd operates in the Electronic parts and equipment sector.
	
	In addition to historical fundamental analyses, the complete report available to purchase compares Vitec Holdings Co Ltd with three other
	
			companies in this sector in Japan:
		
	Tokyo Electron Device Ltd
	
		(2017
	sales of 131.86 billion Japanese Yen [US$1.20  billion]
		of which 87%
		was Semiconductor&Electronic Devices Bus.),
	
	Kanaden Corporation
	
		(122.98 billion Japanese Yen [US$1.12  billion]
		of which 36%
		was FA business system), and
	
	Tomen Devices Corporation
	
		(156.68 billion Japanese Yen [US$1.42  billion]
		of which 52%
		was Operating Segment Oversea).
	
	Sales Analysis. 
	Vitec Holdings Co Ltd reported sales of ¥138.84 billion (US$1.26 billion)
		for the
		
			fiscal
		
		year ending
		March of 2017.
	
		This
		
			represents
		
			a
			
			decrease of 4.5%
		
		 versus 2016, when the company's sales were ¥145.42 billion.
	
		Contributing to the drop in overall sales was the 20.5% decline
		in Device Business, from ¥136.72 billion to ¥108.70 billion.
		.
		
					However, these declines were partially offset by the increase in sales of
					Environment Energy Business (up 47.6% to ¥12.83 billion)
				
			.
		

	




 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










